		<description>In the ever-expanding attempts to fight back the Insectoid nightmare, creative solutions have consistently been proposed all across the galaxy. One of these is the Fire-Bellied Toad, which is simply a toad that literally shoots fire. Fire-Bellied Toads carry a natural internal heating system, making them able to survive in any environment, no matter how cold. \n \n A toad is a type of frog with dry, leathery skin, (usually) short legs, and large bumps on their back. They are divided into the "true toads", which all come from the taxnomic family &lt;i>Bufonidae&lt;/i> , and the nine species of "false toads", the latter endemic only to Old Earth's Chile and Thailand. The fire-bellied toad falls under the former, as a true Bufonidae toad.</description>
